The compounding calculation is on a semi-annual basis: hence, the interest rate of 8.4% will be divided by 2 to determine the rate to be used.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Rate} &= \dfrac{0.084}{2}
\\[10pt]
&= {4.2\%}
\end{aligned}$$

Therefore the semi-annual rate to be used is 4.2%

Let's now calculate the future value.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Future value} &=\$3,100\times(1 + .042)^{34}
\\[5pt]
&= \$3,100\times4.050442252
\\[5pt]
&= \boxed{\bf\$12,556.37}
\end{aligned}$$

**Therefore, the $3,100 after 17 years, if the interest rate is 8.4% compounded semi-annually, is $12,556.37.**
